    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Shallow saucer-shaped plates used in Christian liturgy on which the large host rests on the altar at times before and after consecration. For a dish or bowl used to hold the hosts during distribution to the faithful, use "communion bowls."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
